First of all, the code is using the locale to set the currency formatter. For instance in 
DefaultInvoiceFormatter:

```
 public String getFormattedPaidAmount() {
        final NumberFormat number = NumberFormat.getCurrencyInstance(locale);
        return number.format(getPaidAmount().doubleValue());
 }
```

The number format returned is based on the locale which is 'good' so it knows how to display the dots, comma, ... but wrong it comes to display the currency symbol.
